cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CC 

This paper deals with network coding, which is a topic related to computer networks. The paper specifically focuses on inter-session network coding, which involves multiple sources transmitting data to sets of clients over a wireline overlay network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). 

The paper also deals with rate allocation and optimization, which are topics related to information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category. 

The paper proposes a novel framework for efficient rate allocation, which involves solving an optimization problem. This makes cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a likely category as well. 

The paper also evaluates the proposed solution in different network topologies, which involves simulation and analysis. This makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category. 

Finally, the paper deals with network coding solutions for concurrent multicast sessions, which involves communication protocols. This makes cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible category as well.
